- The year 2022 is specifically selected, implying a focus on recent weather data; 
- Atmospheric pressure is an important metric in weather analysis and is commonly used to forecast weather patterns; 
- The requirement for at least one recorded weather metric ensures that only stations with some level of data quality are included in the results.

sql:
SELECT access_type, COUNT(*) AS access_count
FROM access_logs
GROUP BY access_type;

SELECT AVG(metric_value) AS average_temperature
FROM weather_metrics
WHERE metric_type = 'temperature';

SELECT access_date
FROM access_logs
ORDER BY access_date DESC;

SELECT metadata_value AS longitude, elevation
FROM weather_stations_metadata
WHERE metadata_key = 'longitude';

SELECT calibration_value
FROM instrumentation_calibration
WHERE uncertainty > 0.03;
